definitions.definition: To remove from the set of resources put aside for ( allocated to) a particular user or purpose.
examples: Empty out your locker; it will be deallocated at the end of the day.
Computer programs should deallocate memory they no longer need, releasing it back to the system.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To remove from the set of resources put aside for ( allocated to) a particular user or purpose.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , computing ) To return previously allocated memory .
